		<td><b>Next steps</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'll have a nice chuck of time on my hands to work on my emulator this weekend, and want to make the most of it.  Using NesTest I've managed to get all of the opcodes implemented.  What should I tackle next?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Thu Feb 21, 2013 8:46 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Next steps</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Get PPU timing working: run 3 dots every CPU cycle, run a scanline every 341 dots, implement port $2000, and make an NMI every 262 scanlines. Observe what the game tries to write to $2006 and $2007. This just might be enough to get games to start booting and writing to $4000-$4015, at which point you can start audio emulation.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
